notesStmt.note: Damp entry at lower corner in the first half of the manuscript. Some dark tidemarks.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 33 34; written lines: 33 34; Uniform layout. Catchwords on every page in the earlier part, and at the end of quires in the latter part. Headings and initial words in square characters. The contents of folios 53v-54v crossed out and duplicated on folio 55r sqq.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental semi-cursive scripts of the 15th century. Yitsḥaḳ: his name marked off on folio 128v, 194v, 195v.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Mikhlol Yofi. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2858.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: R. N. Rabinowitz: purchased by the British Museum from him on 18 April 1885: inscribed, folio [206v] (fse002v).
